99.1	Krakatoa	Krakatoa	Krakatoa , and the volcano as a whole. The volcano exploded in 1883, killing 40,000 people; some estimates put the death toll much higher. The explosion is considered to be the loudest sound ever heard in modern history, with reports of it being heard nearly 3,000 miles (4,800 km) from its point of origin. The shock wave from the explosion was recorded on barographs around the globe.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/49/Krakatoa_eruption_lithograph.jpg/280px-Krakatoa_eruption_lithograph.jpg
